Kaizer Chiefs coach Steve Komphela is famous for giving cryptic answers to questions in interviews after matches. Most recently after being asked whether he was relieved to have finally had a win after a string of draws, the coach launched into what could almost be described as a form of free-verse poetry about &#8220;emotional intelligence&#8221; being &#8220;something we have to carry because the difference between chalk and cheese, much as they&#8217;re white, is huge&#8221;. He also spoke about &#8220;going under the roof&#8221;. Watch the video with some humorous reactions spliced into it below: